Taiwan's trade surplus widened to 4.18billion U.S. Dlrs in the first quarter of 1987 from 3.05billion a year ago, the government statistics department said.    First quarter exports rose to 11.25 billion U.S. Dlrs from8.38 billion in the same period in 1986. Imports rose to 7.08billion from 5.33 billion last year.    The March trade surplus was 1.45 billion dlrs compared with1.32 billion in February and 1.02 billion in March 1986.Exports rose to 4.07 billion U.S. Dlrs from 3.85 billion inFebruary and 2.99 billion in March last year. Imports were 2.61billion dlrs against 2.53 billion in February and 1.96 billionin March 1986. REUTER&#3;